Heat the @oil{1%tbsp} in a deep saucepan and fry the @chopped{400%g} @onion{1%large} over a medium heat until tender. Add the @garlic{1%clove} and @tomato pur√©e{1%tbsp}, stirring for ~{1-2%min}s until combined. Sprinkle in the spices and cook for another ~{1%min}.

Tip in the chopped tomatoes, half fill the @can{400%g} with water, and add to the pan. Pour in the @stock{500%ml} and simmer on a medium heat for ~{10-15%min}s, uncovered. Season, then whizz using a hand blender until smooth. Add the beans and @red pepper{1}, and cook for another ~{15%min}s until the pepper is tender.

Serve in bowls topped with a small pile of @tortilla chips{} and a lime wedge.
